        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): tool calls use bound account outside inbound messages",
        "body": "Closes #96657\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Feishu resource tool calls outside inbound Feishu messages could run without `ctx.agentAccountId` and then fall back to the global `channels.feishu.defaultAccount`, even when the active session or current agent already had a Feishu binding for another account.\n\nIn multi-account Feishu deployments, that can route wiki, drive, permission, bitable, document, or app-scope tool calls through the wrong app credential. Operators then see cross-tenant permission failures such as Feishu `99991672` or HTTP 403 even though the current agent/session is bound to the correct Feishu account.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change keeps the explicit and contextual account choices intact, then checks Feishu bindings before falling back to the configured default account. The resulting tool-account precedence is:\n\n1. explicit tool `accountId`\n2. valid contextual `ctx.agentAccountId`\n3. unique Feishu account bound to the current `ctx.sessionKey` in runtime conversation bindings\n4. configured Feishu route binding for the current agent/session from `bindings[]`\n5. configured `channels.feishu.defaultAccount`\n6. existing required-tool-family fallback\n\nIf a session is bound to multiple runtime Feishu accounts, the tool now fails with an ambiguity error instead of silently using `defaultAccount`. Configured route bindings are resolved through the plugin SDK routing facade, so the Feishu plugin still stays on the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` boundary.\n\n## User Impact\n\nFeishu agents that perform scheduled, relayed, heartbeat, or other non-inbound work can now route resource tool calls through the Feishu account bound to the current runtime conversation or configured agent route. This reduces wrong-account tool execution in multi-tenant setups while preserving explicit account overrides and existing default-account fallback behavior for unbound sessions.\n\n## Evidence\n\nAdded focused coverage for the tool-account routing behavior:\n\n- a Feishu wiki tool call without `agentAccountId` uses the current session's runtime Feishu binding before `defaultAccount`\n- a Feishu wiki tool call without `agentAccountId` and without a runtime conversation binding uses the configured `bindings[]` Feishu account before `defaultAccount`\n- a session with multiple runtime Feishu account bindings is rejected as ambiguous instead of falling back to `defaultAccount`\n\nFocused configured-binding proof:\n\n```text\nConfig: defaultAccount=a, bindings[] routes agent main + channel feishu to account b\nContext: sessionKey=agent:main:feishu:configured, ctx.agentAccountId unset, runtime conversation bindings empty\nObserved: registered feishu_wiki tool constructs the Lark client with account b (mock appId app-b), not defaultAccount a\n```\n\nValidation run locally:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/tool-account-routing.test.ts` - passed, 1 file / 27 tests\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/tool-account-routing.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/docx.account-selection.test.ts extensions/feishu/src/tool-account.test.ts` - passed, 3 files / 34 tests\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions` - passed\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` - passed\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm test:extension feishu` - passed, 73 files / 973 tests\n- `git diff --check` - passed\n\nOne earlier default-worker run of `pnpm test:extension feishu` exited on Windows with process code `3221226505` and no failing test output; rerunning the full Feishu extension lane with `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1` passed.\n\nAI-assisted: Prepared and reviewed with Codex GPT-5.5 xhigh assistance; I reviewed the diff and understand the account-routing changes.\r\n",
